 K = \frac{ \vec{l}_p \vec{l}^T_p}{\lambda_p} ;\qquad E = \vec{l}_p \vec{l}^T_p 
E-\lambda K =\frac{\lambda_p-\lambda}{\lambda_p}\vec{l}_p \vec{l}^T_p
(E-\lambda K)^{-1} =\frac{\lambda_p}{\lambda_p - \lambda}\vec{l}_p \vec{l}^T_p
(E-\lambda K)^{-1}(E-\lambda K) =\frac{\lambda_p}{\lambda_p - \lambda}\cdot \frac{\lambda_q-\lambda}{\lambda_q}\vec{l}_p \color{blue}{\vec{l}^T_p \vec{l}_q} \vec{l}^T_q = \frac{\lambda_p}{\lambda_p - \lambda}\cdot \frac{\lambda_q-\lambda}{\lambda_q}\vec{l}_p \color{blue}{\delta_{pq}} \vec{l}^T_q = E
 K \rightarrow K(x,x) = \vec{x}^T \frac{ \vec{l}_p \vec{l}^T_p}{\lambda_p} \vec{x} 
