\vec{y}=L\vec{x}
 K(x,x)=y^T \frac{L\vec{l}_p \vec{l}^T_p L^T}{\lambda_p} y = \sum_{p=1}^n \frac{\vec{y}^T \vec{y}}{\lambda_p}
\big(E(x,x)-\lambda K(x,x)\big)^{-1} = \vec{x}^T \frac{\lambda_p}{\lambda_p - \lambda} \vec{l}_p \vec{l}^T_p \vec{x}= \vec{y}^T \frac{\lambda_p}{\lambda_p - \lambda} \color{green}{L\vec{l}_p \vec{l}^T_p L^T} \vec{y} =\sum_p^n \frac{\lambda_p}{\lambda_p - \lambda} y_p^2
